[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering native image testing**\n\nI’m wondering if the Native image in this repository is set up to run all tests. It compiles, but it implies that tests should execute under Native Image by default. The existing test for VMSupport likely runs natively. If I try adding `jdk.hotspot.agent` compile arguments, it might fail due to a missing module. I could use JUnit’s `@EnabledOnJre`, but I need to think about dynamic coverage and possibly creating a helper that uses JVM input arguments.\n\n**Considering native image processing**\n\nI realize I need a native image if the `java.class.path` lacks the test class, which would cause the process to exit with a nonzero value. I wonder if I could avoid this by checking `isNativeImageRuntime`, but I'm not sure if that would work. An alternative could be to build a native image that includes the test class, but then I question if the `java.class.path` property points to the native image. It's a bit tricky!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_097a8ff8b89283fa016a243364bf6c8197bccce94c3fc69010\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJDOedhhzEvjUTFlqdUyybKyXtJlfxF53BVb-j4q5qhIvCuTod2_u3y7iJb_uiOipvVkgAM51Pf1Ii1tYWiOWEKlV_LgttwgH89UTaP0hLuKDi4_1pdutOtQAK1G9jQLxaDEvyCgLZCZj3u3Ju7Ws7i64_xAxkvKTYPx1Wx-Uz91hgUt1CJeiKK-E7wYlkxjMisUjlSGRX5WMv7K5C0bfh9b2xUVJri2r8iPxGn4sWJFl6M_nARkMCMYcPwWrV5_h15P1Mdpg194v92274ZE0b3FplphXt2CR7xQJnwrG0jJArLctANJM14RHASFuxQTv-3_V0LCu0qI0rabmSuQHGpvKmlLs8GK7_oNdyWhR5tJJrBr1Fd-2R5AUZNMqaJ1YSnascYqq_95q7krynJcQ9kW305K43Jl_wPjV9zUk9bQj8AGiGKDYk1MzGDktdUbyfUhUCjwltUA0NPBE8IqQrKCrr4jo-N6tbNqUepgXMjFtZNmaG9d9HDPNh4xzOJW3IJIu_f9AHyuRE5XKwCbdfE7FwFCKZUpcfyUngMgCy7p_Imq91BMRMw7yfEUKYNtqYuM1MrJ1dYNl_L0U1KY8L_AjRRqQz7uGOncVQK84CQMK5uh3SmXaS1zfVPyyrX0ysiTGVZsGq9-SNkV-3YCeunxQo1MeXJdb3u_l7NP1V8NqaKubeeXueS49n-q-Rsw_4ROSuF8VGiAk8KJb4QGY0zB8evaUww6qKPK_f4bz3FIdJtPl72VAVELWLouzK5