y test? Though I realize tests can’t assert known broken paths. I’m pondering that full coverage might not improve under JDK25 due to removed API support; achieving that would require a dependency that's unavailable.\\n\\nMaybe commenting in the test to clarify why certain lines remain could help?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "I can’t safely improve coverage beyond the 4 newly covered call sites in the current JDK 25 test environment.\n\nReason:\n- `HS_SA_CompressedReferencesProcessor.process()` must successfully resolve these methods before it can continue:\n\n  ```java\n  universeClass.getMethod(\"getNarrowOopBase\");\n  universeClass.getMethod(\"getNarrowOopShift\");\n  ```\n\n- On the current JDK, `jdk.hotspot.agent`’s real `sun.jvm.hotspot.memory.Universe` no longer exposes those legacy public methods.\n- Because line 52 fails, execution cannot reach:\n  - line 53,\n  - the Java 8 klass-reference method lookup block at lines 61–64,\n  - or any of the `Method.invoke(...)` calls at lines 69–89.\n\nThe remaining call sites are therefore only reachable with an older HotSpot Serviceability Agent API, e.g. the Java 8-era `sa-jdi.jar`/SA classes that still expose the narrow-oop and narrow-klass accessors.\n\nPer the rules, I should not create fake/shadow `sun.jvm.hotspot.*` classes or generated replacements just to satisfy coverage. Since the needed legacy SA API is not available on the current test classpath/JDK, the remaining call sites should be left unreached with this explanation.\n\nNo additional code or metadata changes were made.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_097a8ff8b89283fa016a24353460548197800adadbde642a30\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2360, "output": 1134, "cacheRead": 62464, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 65958, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780757791442, "respo